<br>
I'm just looking for tips...rules of thumb...and possible simple things that I'm overlooking.  In groups, I'm almost always with an SK of one race or another(I'm in an all evil guild on the roleplay server*grin*), and I'm perfectly happy letting them pull....but I really want to be able to not bring 400 things down on my groups, so any hints, tips, suggestions, would be great. <p><center><a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/bsarscorner"><img src="http://sarshouse.homestead.com/files/images/sarsig.jpg"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/15/02 5:43:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1778.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What makes a good puller?</span><hr size=1> A good sense of space helps.  If you can figure out how close you can approach a mob without agroing.  Check line of sight.  Can you see him, but not the others around him?  The more isolated the line of sight is, the better your odds of pulling solo.  By that I mean, if none of his buddies can see you, but you can see him, the chances are better you'll get just him.<br>
<br>
How large is the assist range on the mobs?  Can you figure out how many are probably going to respond if you pull?  If you can, alert your group so they know what to expect.  Sometimes pulling using proximaty is better than pulling with an arrow, depending on how close you can get without getting more mobs in your line of sight.  Ideally you would want to get just close enough that he agros on you but not close enough to agro the rest of his buddies.<br>
<br>
Most of it is just experience and being aware of space. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A> at: 7/16/02 6:03:55 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utarlor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tarlor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/15/02 5:43:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1778.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What makes a good puller?</span><hr size=1> know the area, mob pathing, aggro proximity - this all goes without saying.<br>
