One example I can think of right off the top of my head is the alchemist acolyte in chardok.  He sits right next to the herbalist shack.<br>
First time I pulled him I plunked an arrow into him from max range.  He pathed around the herb shack and brought like 10 friends.<br>
Once I learned to get closer to him and hit him with an arrow, he paths straight at me.  He comes with no more than 1 add.<br>
<br>
Pathing is all about how the mobs gets from his point to you.  If pathing sends the mob into other mobs, try changing your point it may make him path differently and avoid adds.<br>
